# ZenetHunter CODEOWNERS
# Location: keep this file in the repo root (or .github/ or docs/). GitHub uses the first it finds on the default branch.
# Order matters: the last matching pattern wins. Keep general rules first, specific rules later.
# Teams must exist in the same org and have at least write permission to be requested for review.
# Docs: https://docs.github.com/articles/about-code-owners

# ---- Defaults (fallback) ----
# Everything defaults to Maintainers if no specific owner matches
*                                   @ZJ-Dragon/maintainers

# ---- Backend ----
/backend/                            @ZJ-Dragon/backend @ZJ-Dragon/maintainers
/backend/**                          @ZJ-Dragon/backend @ZJ-Dragon/maintainers

# ---- Frontend ----
/frontend/                           @ZJ-Dragon/frontend @ZJ-Dragon/maintainers
/frontend/**                         @ZJ-Dragon/frontend @ZJ-Dragon/maintainers

# ---- Defender (future subdir if separated) ----
/defender/                           @ZJ-Dragon/defender @ZJ-Dragon/maintainers
/defender/**                         @ZJ-dragon/defender @ZJ-Dragon/maintainers

# ---- CI / Ops ----
/.github/workflows/**                @ZJ-Dragon/ci @ZJ-Dragon/maintainers

# ---- Documentation ----
/docs/                               @ZJ-Dragon/docs @ZJ-Dragon/maintainers
/docs/**                             @ZJ-Dragon/docs @ZJ-Dragon/maintainers

# ---- Sensitive policies & top-level files ----
/SECURITY.md                         @ZJ-Dragon/security @ZJ-Dragon/maintainers
/CODEOWNERS                          @ZJ-Dragon/maintainers
/README.md                           @ZJ-Dragon/docs @ZJ-Dragon/maintainers
/LICENSE                             @ZJ-Dragon/maintainers

# ---- Examples of fine-grained patterns (uncomment/adjust as needed) ----
# Only root-level files (no subdirectories):
# /*                                  @ZJ-Dragon/maintainers
# Specific file types:
# /backend/**.py                      @ZJ-Dragon/backend
# /frontend/**.{ts,tsx,js,jsx}        @ZJ-Dragon/frontend
